  15 Jul 2004; Tom Gall <tgall@gentoo.org> cdparanoia-3.9.8-r1.ebuild:
  stable on ppc64, bug #55563

  01 Jul 2004; Jeremy Huddleston <eradicator@gentoo.org>
  cdparanoia-3.9.8-r1.ebuild:
  virtual/glibc -> virtual/libc

*cdparanoia-3.9.8-r1 (22 Apr 2004)

  23 Apr 2004; Mike Frysinger <vapier@gentoo.org> :
  Add gcc-3.4 patch (#47869 by Tamran Lengyel), fix include path with 
  the new cdda_interface patch (#48776 by Carmine Moleti), and use econf 
  instead of ./configure (me).

  22 Apr 2004; Martin Schlemmer <azarah@gentoo.org>
  cdparanoia-3.9.8-r1.ebuild,
  files/cdparanoia-3.9.8-include-cdda_interface_h.patch:
  cdda_paranoia.h should include cdda_interface_h, else most configure
  scripts testing for support fails (gnome-vfs, etc).

  20 Apr 2004; Jeremy Huddleston <eradicator@gentoo.org>
  cdparanoia-3.9.8.ebuild:
  Added IUSE.

  07 Mar 2004; Stephen P. Becker <geoman@gentoo.org> cdparanoia-3.9.8.ebuild:
  Added ~mips keyword.

  28 Jan 2004; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> cdparanoia-3.9.8.ebuild:
  stable on ia64

  18 Jan 2003; Bryon Roche <kain@kain.org> ChangeLog, cdparanoia-3.9.8.ebuild :
  
  Added ppc to keywords.

  06 Dec 2002; Rodney Rees <manson@gentoo.org> : changed sparc ~sparc keywords
 
  13 Apr 2002; M.Schlemmer <azarah@gentoo.org> cdparanoia-3.9.8.ebuild :

  Fix the creation of the invalid dir, /usr/share/man1.

*cdparanoia-3.9.8 (1 Feb 2002)

  1 Feb 2002; G.Bevin <gbevin@gentoo.org> ChangeLog :
  
  Added initial ChangeLog which should be updated whenever the package is
  updated in any way. This changelog is targetted to users. This means that the
  comments should well explained and written in clean English. The details about
  writing correct changelogs are explained in the skel.ChangeLog file which you
  can find in the root directory of the portage repository.
